textDelta: The real power within the United Nations is located in the Security Council. The five permanent members (China, France, Russia, United Kingdom, United States) have veto powers and, therefore, can block any resolution. The General Assembly, meanwhile, can only make recommendations. The Security Council is responsible for authorizing the use of force, imposing sanctions, and approving peacekeeping operations. Its decisions, therefore, have direct, immediate, and far-reaching consequences. The percentage of the world's land area that was forested in 2015 was 31.1 percent, according to data released Wednesday by the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (FAO). The FAO's Global Forest Resources Assessment 2015 (FRA 2015), which tracks global forest resources since 1990, found that the world's forests continue to shrink. "Forests continue to face pressure from agriculture, livestock, and urban expansion, as well as fires and climate change," said FAO Director-General José Graziano da Silva in a press release.
